summary:
Rewatching the body-switcharoo bit of Good Omens and damn Michael Sheen is such a great actor.
David Tennant doing...
body:
Rewatching the body-switcharoo bit of Good Omens and damn Michael Sheen is such a great actor.

David Tennant doing Aziraphale-as-Crowley is like “OK, let me dial down the Tennant swagger about 10%, that should be good to approximate the angel, right?”

But Sheen just leans into it. He IS Crowley in Aziraphale’s body. The level of barely concealed hatred that he regards the Angels with. Angels who threw him out of Heaven and then proceeded to kill kids, nail a carpenter to a cross for saying that people should treat each other well, Angels who were desperate for their big apocalyptic War. It’s simmering below the surface as he tries to arrange his face into Aziraphale’s face. The way his body takes on bits of Tennant’s long-limbed swagger, his barely interested regard for the contents of Aziraphel’s bookshop. All of it. Every little bit. It’s Crowley in Aziraphale’s skin, trying desperately to make himself look enough like an Angel to pass and not quite succeeding.

summary: You have to find this stuff, you have to find things, these fragments that you hold to yourself. They become like a life raft,...
text: You have to find this stuff, you have to find things, these fragments that you hold to yourself. They become like a life raft, especially as time goes on. As I’ve got older I’ve realised there is a thin line between surviving this life and going under and the things that keep you afloat are these fragments, these things that are meaningful to you. And what’s meaningful to you will be not meaningful to someone else. But whatever it is that matters to you, it doesn’t matter what it is, go and find them and find some way to hold them close to you. Go and get it. Because those are the things that keep you afloat. Whatever it is. These are the fragments I have shored against my ruins.
source: Michael Sheen, delivering the most beautiful and heartfelt little speech at the end of David Tennant’s podcast
